 p5.fab Quickstart # Here are a couple of ways to get started with p5.fab.
Online Editor # Using Chrome1, open the online editor. Design your artifact! You can start from one of the examples; try changing some of the values in the sketch to see what happens to the resulting object. Physically connect your computer to your fabrication machine2 with a USB cable and click &lsquo;Connect&rsquo;. Start making! Press &lsquo;Print&rsquo; to start streaming commands to your machine. Be sure to keep an eye out for anything that goes wrong; there&rsquo;s no guarantee that your code will &lsquo;work&rsquo; in any conventional sense, but that&rsquo;s part of the fun! We use serial communication to communicate with the machine; Chrome is the only browser which supports WebSerial, which let&rsquo;s us get up and running even quicker!&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
Check out the Machine Compatability Page for more information on what machines are currently supported.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
